<p>November 1916<br/>afternoon with drizling rain, which lasted most of the night.<br/>12th   A heavy barrage was carried out by the artillery early this morning &amp; it is rumoured that an attack is to be <strike>delivered</strike> made this morning.  The weather is still very foggy &amp; cold, &amp; we have been issued with sheep skin vests &amp; extra woolen clothing<br/>We have been unable to get our infantry fatigue party this morning as they are going into the line tonight, but we have been given another small party for the afternoon.<br/>About 7 P.M. Fritz dropped a shell in our camp about a dozen yds. from our hut, but no one was hurt.</p>
